@startuml svc-safety-compliance--post-incidents

!include ../theme.puml
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #dc2626
}

header [[/microservices/svc-safety-compliance/#integration-context ⬆ svc-safety-compliance Integration Context]]

title POST /incidents\nFile a safety incident report\n<size:10><color:#7c3aed>ARCHITECT OVERRIDE — enriched with severity classification and escalation</color></size>

participant "Client" as Client [[/applications/]]
participant "API Gateway" as GW [[/actors/#api-gateway]] #E0F2FE
participant "svc-safety-compliance" as Svc [[/microservices/svc-safety-compliance/]] #FEE2E2
participant "Guest Profiles" as GP [[/microservices/svc-guest-profiles/]] #EDE9FE
participant "Guide Mgmt" as GM [[/microservices/svc-guide-management/]] #E0E7FF
participant "Notifications" as Ntfy [[/microservices/svc-notifications/]] #F1F5F9
database "PostgreSQL" as DB [[/microservices/svc-safety-compliance/#data-store]] #FEF9C3

note over Svc
  [[/services/api/svc-safety-compliance.html View in Swagger UI]]
end note

Client -> GW : POST /incidents
activate GW #dc2626
GW -> Svc : route request
activate Svc #dc2626

note right of Svc : Validate incident report\n(incident_type, guest_id,\nlocation, description required)\n\nClassify severity:\nMINOR | MODERATE | SERIOUS | CRITICAL

== Guest Contact Information ==

Svc -> GP : [[/microservices/svc-guest-profiles/#get-guestsguest_id-get-guest-profile GET /guests/{guest_id}]]
activate GP #EDE9FE
GP --> Svc : Guest profile\n(name, emergency contacts,\nmedical notes)
deactivate GP

== Guide Identification ==

Svc -> GM : [[/microservices/svc-guide-management/#get-guidesguide_id-get-guide-details GET /guides/{guide_id}]]
activate GM #E0E7FF
GM --> Svc : Guide details\n(name, certifications,\nassigned trip)
deactivate GM

== Severity-Based Alert Routing ==

alt CRITICAL — Life-threatening injury
    note right of Svc #FEE2E2 : Route to:\n- Safety Director (immediate)\n- Emergency Response team\n- External authorities if needed\n- Guest emergency contacts\n\nTrigger incident lock-down\nFreeze all related records
else SERIOUS — Injury requiring medical attention
    note right of Svc #FEF3C7 : Route to:\n- Safety Manager\n- Operations team\n- Guide supervisor\n\nRequire follow-up within 24h
else MODERATE — Equipment failure, near-miss
    note right of Svc #FEF3C7 : Route to:\n- Safety team inbox\n- Guide (acknowledgement)\n\nRequire follow-up within 72h
else MINOR — Procedural observation
    note right of Svc #D1FAE5 : Route to:\n- Safety team inbox only\n\nQueued for weekly review
end

== Database ==

group Transaction boundary (PostgreSQL)
    Svc -> DB : INSERT INTO safety_incidents\n(incident_id, incident_type,\nseverity, guest_id, guide_id,\nlocation, description,\nstatus = OPEN)
    activate DB #FEF9C3
    DB --> Svc : Created row
    deactivate DB

    Svc -> DB : INSERT INTO incident_timeline\n(event_type = FILED,\nfiled_by, timestamp)
    activate DB #FEF9C3
    DB --> Svc : Created row
    deactivate DB
end

== Async Alert ==

Svc ->> Ntfy : [[/microservices/svc-notifications/#post-notifications-send-a-notification Send safety alert]]\n(recipients determined by severity)

Svc --> GW : 201 Created\n(incident_id, severity,\nstatus, alert_recipients)
deactivate Svc
GW --> Client : 201 Created
deactivate GW

@enduml
